% movefile-note setup movefile tests
% 
% Notes for movefile tests.
%
% The movefile01.oml script creates some directores and files which are used by the
% other movefile*.oml tests scripts.
%
% Creates a 'movefile' directory under 'FileManipulation'
% Under the 'movefile' directory, creates the following entries:
% <dir> dir1
% <dir> dir2
% <file> test1.txt
% <file> test2.txt
%
% movefile01.oml should be the first script to run.
%
% movefile99.oml script deletes the above files and directories, including the 'movefile'
% directory under 'FileManipulation'.
% movefile99.oml should be the last script to be run for movefile testing.

% Other movefilenn.oml scripts perform the tests.  Some tests add new files and directories.
% Each existing test and any new tests should restore the 'movefile' directory to the above state.
% Failure to do so may cause later tests to appear to fail as their test logs may no longer
% match the reference log.  
% Restoring the movefile test directory to the above state will help avoid false failed tests.


returndir = pwd;
cd FileManipulation

mkdir movefile
cd movefile
dir

disp('Create test directories')
command = 'mkdir dir1'
eval(command)
command = 'mkdir dir2'
eval(command)

disp('Create test files')
command = 'system(''echo test1 > test1.txt'')'
eval(command)
command = 'system(''echo test2 > test2.txt'')'
eval(command)

dir
cd(returndir)